<p><b>What is the instrument used to measure chemical analysis?</b> Mass Spectrometer (MS) The fragments resulting from the breakdown of chemical structures when substances are bombarded by electrons is specific to each substance. Using this property, mass spectrographs measure the weight (mass) of the fragments, thus identifying the substance in question.</p>
